          <p>MR. LEO GLAVINE : Mr. Speaker, my question is for the Minister of Health and Wellness. Last Thursday, just prior to all of the flurry that surrounds opening day at the Legislature, the minister sent out a press release that his government plans to hire seven auditors who will in turn support other auditors in the districts. According to the release, the hiring of seven auditors will ensure we receive better front-line health care. Can the minister please tell the House how the hiring of seven auditors will provide better front-line health care?</p>
