          <from>HON. DAVID WILSON</from>
          <p>HON. DAVID WILSON : Mr. Speaker, I think it's extremely important that Nova Scotians recognize that we need to ensure that the money they provide government is spent in the most appropriate way. We spend $3.8 billion on the health care budget. I think Nova Scotians would appreciate that an audit is done with the district health authorities across this province. (Applause)</p>
