          <p>MR. WILSON : Mr. Speaker, I said earlier in a response from a previous question, the one thing that we recognized here in Nova Scotia when we came to government in 2009, was that we had to do things differently, especially in health care, and we're doing things differently. We're not doing it the Liberal way - cutting and slashing, firing doctors and nurses. We're not doing it the Progressive Conservative way, when you just stick your head in the sand and ignore all the issues.</p>
